So here's how I evaluated Charm: In a mono blue deck I slotted it in as an instant speed draw spell. If you look at it as nothing more than a draw 2 at instant speed, it's pretty solid. Then it also has the option instead to counter a spell, or steal a Sol Ring or Marit Lage token. So worst case scenario in mono blue where the pips don't matter it's probably good enough just as a draw, but it has really excellent, versatile upside.
Actually, I was seeing how many of the top 100 or so of each permanent type it could steal (ie was 1 CMC or less).
